Sentencas: This work strives to improve the performance of SrSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-delta (SSNC) cathode by introducing A-site cation deficiency up to 10 mol%.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Three different Sr-deficient compositions, i.e., Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-delta (S1-xSNC, x=0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) including the non-deficient analogue, SSNC are prepared.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Powder X-ray diffraction patterns indicate that the original cubic perovskite structure is retained.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient between 50 degrees C and 900 degrees C increases progressively with increasing Sr deficiency, consistent with the beta-oxygen release profiles trend.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities for SSNC, S0.98SNC, S0.95SNC and S0.9SNC show a maximum-type profile against increasing temperature, i.e., semiconducting behavior followed by metallic behavior.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Despite the consistent increase in the oxygen non-stoichiometry with increasing Sr deficiency, the oxygen reduction reaction performance increases in the order of SSNC, S0.9SNC, S0.98SNC and S0.95SNC.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: That the highest oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) performance is demonstrated by S0.95SNC indicates the trade-off between the increase in the concentration of oxygen vacancies and the formation of the phase impurities.
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 650 degrees C, S0.95SNC shows an area specific resistance of 0.017 Omega cm(2) (from symmetric cell test) and a peak power density of 1263 mW cm(-2) (from single fuel cell test on a Ni-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) anode supported SDC electrolyte).
Titulo: Evaluation of A-site deficient Sr1-xSc0.175Nb0.025Co0.8O3-δ (x=0, 0.02, 0.05 and 0.1) perovskite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
